{% extends "template.njk" %}

{% import "_pattern_macros/testcard.njk" as testcard %}

{% block title %}Get Started{% endblock %}

{% block main %}

<div class="container mb-5">
  <h1>Get Started</h1>
  <p class="lead mb-4">This page will provide the details of setting up a developer environment on your system. Before you start, make sure you have the latest version of Node.js installed on your system.</p>
  <hr>
</div>


<div class="container">
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">1. Create a new folder. This will be your project directory. It doesn't matter what you call this folder but make sure it's relevant and memorable to you.</h2> 
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">2. Open a terminal window in the project folder and type: <kbd>npm init -y</kbd></h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">3. Now type: <kbd>npm install @11ty/eleventy</kbd></h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">4. Create the file: <code>.eleventy.js</code></h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">5. Insert the following code into <code>.eleventy.js</code>:</h2>
  
<pre class="prettyprint lang-js">let Nunjucks = require(&quot;nunjucks&quot;);

module.exports = function(eleventyConfig) {

  let nunjucksEnvironment = new Nunjucks.Environment(
    new Nunjucks.FileSystemLoader(&quot;src/_includes&quot;)
  );

  eleventyConfig.setLibrary(&quot;njk&quot;, nunjucksEnvironment);

  return {
    markdownTemplateEngine: 'njk',
    dataTemplateEngine: 'njk',
    htmlTemplateEngine: 'njk',
    dir: {
      input: &quot;src&quot;,
      output: &quot;public&quot;
    },
  };

};</pre>
  
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">6. Insert the following code to the <code>scripts</code> block in <code>package.json</code>:</h2>
  
<pre class="prettyprint">"start": "eleventy --serve",
"build": "eleventy"</pre>
  
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">7. Create directory <code>src</code> and in <code>src</code>, create directory <code>_includes</code></h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">8. In <code>_includes</code>, create the file <code>template.njk</code></h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">9. In <code>template.njk</code>, paste in some boilerplate HTML with the addition of <br><kbd>{% raw %}{% block main %}{% endblock %}{% endraw %}</kbd> somewhere in the body (i.e. inside the <kbd>&lt;main&gt;</kbd> tag)</h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">10. In <code>src</code>, create the file <code>index.njk</code></h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">11. In <code>index.njk</code>, enter the following:</h2>
  <pre class="prettyprint lang-html">{% raw %}{% extends "template.njk" %}
{% block main %}
  &lt;p&gt;This can be any html - its purpose is to test whether everything is working correctly.&lt;/p&gt;
{% endblock %}{% endraw %}</pre>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">12. Run <kbd>npm start</kbd> to check if everything works (you should see a page at <i>localhost:8080</i>)</h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">13. Run <kbd>npm install sass npm-run-all</kbd></h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">14. Replace the content of the <code>scripts</code> block in <code>package.json</code> with the following:</h2>
<pre class="prettyprint">"watch:sass": "sass --watch src/sass:public/css",
"build:sass": "sass src/sass:public/css",
"watch:eleventy": "eleventy --serve",
"build:eleventy": "eleventy",
"start": "npm-run-all build:sass --parallel watch:*",
"build": "npm-run-all build:*"</pre>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">15. In <code>src</code>, create directory <code>sass</code> and inside, add a <code>style.scss</code> file with some basic styling.</h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">16. Link the CSS in template.njk ( <kbd>&lt;link rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; href=&quot;/css/style.css&quot;&gt;</kbd> )</h2>
  <h2 class="h4 mt-5">17. Insert the following into <code>.eleventy.js</code>, within the <code>module.exports</code> block:</h2>
  <pre class="prettyprint lang-js">eleventyConfig.addWatchTarget("./src/sass/");
eleventyConfig.addPassthroughCopy("./src/img/");</pre>

<h3 class="my-5">Everything should now be fully working!</h2> 

</div>

{% endblock %}
